quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  28,51,"Indeed, We have steadily delivered the Word ňĻof Godňļ to the people so they may be mindful"
  28,52,"ňĻAs forňļ those ňĻfaithfulňļ to whom We had given the Scripture before this ňĻQuranňļ, they do believe in it"
  28,53,"When it is recited to them, they declare, ‚ÄúWe believe in it. This is definitely the truth from our Lord. We had already submitted¬†ňĻevenňļ before this.‚ÄĚ"
  28,54,"These ňĻbelieversňļ will be given a double reward for their perseverance, responding to evil with good, and for donating from what We have provided for them"
  28,55,"When they hear slanderous talk, they turn away from it, saying, ‚ÄúWe are accountable for our deeds and you for yours. Peace ňĻis our only responseňļ to you! We want nothing to do with those who act ignorantly.‚ÄĚ"
  28,56,"You surely cannot guide whoever you like ňĻO Prophetňļ, but it is God Who guides whoever He wills, and He knows best who are ňĻfit to beňļ guided"
  28,57,"They say ňĻto the Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúIf we were to follow ňĻtrueňļ guidance with you, we would certainly be snatched away from our land.‚ÄĚ Have We not established for them a safe haven ňĻin Meccaňļ to which fruits of all kinds are brought as a provision from Us? But most of them do not know ňĻthis favourňļ"
  28,58,"ňĻImagineňļ how many societies We have destroyed that had been spoiled by their ňĻcomfortableňļ living! Those are their residences, never inhabited after them except passingly.¬†And We ňĻaloneňļ were the Successor"
  28,59,"Your Lord would never destroy a society until He had sent to its capital a messenger, reciting Our revelations to them. Nor would We ever destroy a society unless its people persisted in wrongdoing"
  28,60,Whatever ňĻpleasureňļ you have been given is no more than ňĻa fleetingňļ enjoyment and adornment of this worldly life. But what is with God is far better and more lasting. Will you not then understand
  28,61,"Can those to whom We have made a fine promise‚ÄĒwhich they will see fulfilled‚ÄĒbe like those who We have allowed to enjoy the pleasures of this worldly life, but on the Day of Judgment will be brought ňĻfor punishmentňļ"
  28,62,"ňĻWatch forňļ the Day He will call to them, ‚ÄúWhere are those you claimed were My associate-gods?‚ÄĚ"
  28,63,"Those ňĻmisleadersňļ against whom the decree ňĻof tormentňļ is justified will cry, ‚ÄúOur Lord! These ňĻfollowersňļ are the ones we caused to deviate. We led them into deviance, for we ourselves were deviant. We disassociate ourselves ňĻfrom themňļ before You. It was not us that they used to worship.‚ÄĚ"
  28,64,"It will be said ňĻto the disbelieversňļ, ‚ÄúCall upon your associate-gods ňĻfor helpňļ.‚ÄĚ So they will call them, but will receive no response. And they will face the punishment, wishing they had been ňĻrightlyňļ guided"
  28,65,"And ňĻwatch forňļ the Day He will call to them, asking, ‚ÄúWhat response did you give to the messengers?‚ÄĚ"
  28,66,They will be too dumbstruck on that Day to ask one another ňĻfor answersňļ
  28,67,"As for those who repent, believe, and do good ňĻin this worldňļ, it is right to hope that they will be among the successful"
  28,68,Your Lord creates and chooses whatever He wills‚ÄĒthe choice is not theirs. Glorified and Exalted is God above what they associate ňĻwith Himňļ
  28,69,And your Lord knows what their hearts conceal and what they reveal
  28,70,He is God. There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. All praise belongs to Him in this life and the next. All authority is His. And to Him you will ňĻallňļ be returned
  28,71,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúImagine if God were to make the night perpetual for you until the Day of Judgment, which god other than God could bring you sunlight? Will you not then listen?‚ÄĚ"
  28,72,"Ask ňĻthem alsoňļ, ‚ÄúImagine if God were to make the day perpetual for you until the Day of Judgment, which god other than God could bring you night to rest in? Will you not then see?‚ÄĚ"
  28,73,"It is out of His mercy that He has made for you the day and night so that you may rest ňĻin the latterňļ and seek His bounty ňĻin the formerňļ, and perhaps you will be grateful"
  28,74,"And ňĻwatch forňļ the Day He will call to them, ‚ÄúWhere are those you claimed were My associate-gods?‚ÄĚ"
  28,75,"And We will bring forth a witness¬†from every faith-community and ask ňĻthe polytheistsňļ, ‚ÄúShow ňĻUsňļ your proof.‚ÄĚ Then they will ňĻcome toňļ know that the truth is with God ňĻaloneňļ. And whatever ňĻgodsňļ they fabricated will fail them"